cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with template matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a hashing scheme based on consensus set maximization, which can be seen as a randomized hypothesize-and-test algorithm. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is likely as the paper presents a reduction that transforms the problem of searching a nearest neighbor among high-dimensional vectors to searching neighbors among two sets of order sqrt(N) vectors, which can be found efficiently using range search techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper proposes a novel approach to template matching that is efficient and comes with provable performance guarantees. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is also possible as the paper deals with image matching, which is a common problem in computer graphics.
